1 (b) (1) This section applies only to:
2 (i) a grant or contract awarded on or after October 1, 2018;
3 (ii) a multi–year grant or contract awarded before October 1, 2018,
4 if:
5 1. the grant or contract continues to be in effect on or after
6 October 1, 2018; and
7 2. funding for the grant or contract is required to be
8 authorized separately for each fiscal year; and
9 (iii) an extension or a renewal of a grant or contract if the extension
10 or renewal is awarded on or after July 1, 2019.
11 (2) This section applies whether or not the funds awarded through the
12 grant or contract are transferred directly by the State or through a third party to the
13 nonprofit organization.
14 (3) This section does not require the reimbursement of indirect costs
15 incurred under a multi–year grant or contract described under paragraph (1)(ii) of this
16 subsection during any fiscal year that begins before July 1, 2019.
17 (c) If a nonprofit organization is a direct recipient or subrecipient of a grant or
18 contract for the provision of services that is funded wholly with State funds or with a
19 combination of State and other nonfederal funds, the terms of the grant or contract shall
20 allow for reimbursement of indirect costs:
21 (1) at the same rate the nonprofit organization has negotiated and
22 received:
23 (i) for indirect costs under a direct federal award; or
24 (ii) from a nonfederal entity based on the cost principles in Subpart
25 E of OMB Uniform Guidance; or
26 (2) if the nonprofit organization has not negotiated and received an indirect
27 cost rate described in item (1) of this subsection, at a rate [of at least 10%] EQUAL TO THE
28 DE MINIMIS RATE ESTABLISHED IN SUBPART E OF OMB UNIFORM GUIDANCE of the
29 costs that would be considered modified total direct costs under OMB Uniform Guidance.
30 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
31 October 1, 2025.

